'''Chamba Leko''' is one of two languages spoken by the [[Chamba people]], the other being [[Chamba Daka]]. It is a member of the [[Leko languages|Leko]] branch of [[Savanna languages]], and is spoken across the northern [[Nigeria]]n–[[Cameroon]]ian border.

''Chamba'' is also spelled 'Samba', ''Leko'' also 'Leeko', 'Lego' or 'Lekon'. The language is also known as ''Suntai''.

