# Opinions differ on the aspiration of {{IPA|/t͡sʰ, t͡ʃʰ/}}, as it is non-contrastive.{{citation needed|date=April 2017}}
# Opinions differ on how to classify {{IPA|/x/}} and {{IPA|/ɣ/}}; {{Harvcoltxt|Aronson|1990}} classifies them as post-velar, {{Harvcoltxt|Hewitt|1995}} argues that they range from velar to uvular according to context.

Former {{IPA|/qʰ/}} ({{lang|ka|ჴ}}) has merged with {{IPA|/x/}} ({{lang|ka|ხ}}), leaving only the latter.

The glottalization of the ejectives is rather light, and in many romanization systems it is not marked, for transcriptions such as ejective ''p'', ''t'', ''ts'', ''ch'', ''k'' and ''q'', against aspirated ''p‘'', ''t‘'', ''ts‘'', ''ch‘'' and ''k‘'' (as in transcriptions of Armenian).

The coronal occlusives ({{IPA|/tʰ tʼ d n/}}, not necessarily affricates) are variously described as apical dental, laminal alveolar, and "dental".<ref name=ipashosted/>

