{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}} {{Infobox writer | name = Karin Amatmoekrim | image = Amatmoekrim2017.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Amatmoekrim (2017) | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1976|12|25}} | birth_place = [[Paramaribo]], Suriname | occupation = Writer | language = [[Dutch language|Dutch]] | nationality = | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Amsterdam]] | period = | genre = | subject = | movement = | notableworks = | spouse = | partner = | children = | relatives = | awards = [[Black Magic Woman Literature Prize]] (2009) | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = 2004–present | module = | website = {{URL|www.amatmoekrim.com}} | portaldisp = yes }}
'''Karin Amatmoekrim''' (born 25 December 1976) is a [[Suriname]]se writer. She has written five novels and won the 2009 [[Black Magic Woman Literature Prize]] for ''Titus''.
== Biography == Karin Amatmoekrim was born on 25 December 1976 in [[Paramaribo]], Suriname. In 1981, she emigrated from Suriname to the Netherlands and grew up in [[IJmuiden]]. She attended the [[Gymnasium (school)|Gymnasium]] in [[Velsen]], and then studied Modern Literature at the [[University of Amsterdam]], graduating with a thesis on "The ethnicity in Literature in Suriname".<ref>{{Cite web|title=Karin Amatmoekrim|url=http://uitgeverijprometheus.nl/index.php?option=com_pac&view=auteur_detail&id=49295/|publisher=Uitgeverij Prometheus|date=}}</ref>
In 2004, she published her first novel, ''Het knipperleven'' ("The glare of life"), which was enthusiastically received by the press. In 2006, it was followed by ''Wanneer wij samen zijn'' ("When we are together"), a novel based on the story of several generations of the Amatmoekrim family. In 2009 appeared the novel ''Titus''. Amatmoekrim has also published short stories in ''[[De Groene Amsterdammer]]'' and ''[[Vrij Nederland]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Biografie|url=http://www.amatmoekrim.com/site/?page_id=12/|publisher=Karin Amatmoekrim (amatmoekrim.com)|date=}}</ref>
In 2009, she was the first recipient of the [[Black Magic Woman Literature Prize]] for her novel ''Titus''.<ref>Peter le Nobel, "[http://www.nationaleboekenblog.nl/nieuws/amatmoekrim-wint-eerste-black-magic-woman-literatuurprijs/ Amatmoekrim wint eerste Black Magic Woman Literatuurprijs]" (in Dutch), ''Nationaleboekenblog'', 2009. Retrieved 4 September 2015.</ref> Karin is married to Jesse Smit, the founder of the brand FreshCotton. She has two children, Sumina Smit (14) and Lee Benjamin Smit (10).
== Bibliography == *2004: ''Het knipperleven'' (The flash life) *2006: ''Wanneer wij samen zijn'' (When we are together) *2009: ''Titus'' (Titus) *2011: ''Het gym'' (The gymnasium) *2013: ''De man van veel'' (The man of many) *2016: ''Tenzij de vader'' (Unless the father)
