{{Infobox writer | name = Risto Isomäki | image = Risto Isomäki.jpg | caption = Risto Isomäki at [[Helsinki Book Fair]] at October 2007. }}
'''Risto Isomäki''' (born June 8, 1961 in [[Turku]]) is a Finnish author of [[science fiction]] books. His 2005 novel ''The Sands of Sarasvati'' (''Sarasvatin hiekkaa'') was nominated for the [[Finlandia Prize]] in 2005 and won the [[Tähtivaeltaja]] award in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.hs.fi/kulttuuri/artikkeli/Scifi-kirjallisuuden+T%C3%A4htivaeltaja-palkinto+Risto+Isom%C3%A4elle/1135221093032 |title = Scifi-kirjallisuuden Tähtivaeltaja-palkinto Risto Isomäelle |accessdate = 2007-07-12 |work = HS.fi ([[Helsingin Sanomat]])}}</ref> Two of his novels, ''The Sands of Sarasvati'' (Into, 2013) and ''Lithium-6'' (AmazonCrossing, 2015) have been published in English, along with a graphic novel adaptation of ''The Sands of Sarasvati'' (Tammi, 2008).
