The future takes primary endings. ''{{transl|sa|-iṣya-}}'' is added to the stem, both in the active and the middle/passive. {| class="wikitable" |+ Future, Indicative |- !rowspan="2"| Person !colspan="3"| Active !colspan="3"| Middle/Passive |- ! Singular !! Dual !! Plural !! Singular !! Dual !! Plural |- ! '''1.''' | {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyāmi}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyāva}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyāma}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣy(ām}})ai || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyāvahai}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyāmahai}} |- ! '''2.''' | {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyasi}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyathas}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyatha}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyasai}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyaithai}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyadhvai}} |- ! '''3.''' | {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyati}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyatas}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyanti}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyatai}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyaitai}} || {{transl|sa|bhaviṣyantai}} |}
The second or periphrastic future is made by adding suffix ''{{transl|sa|tṝ}}'' to the stem and the short ''as'' 'to be' form, except 3rd person, both singular and plural, having feminine {{transl|sa|ṝ}}-stem nominative endings, e.g., ''bhavi-'' + ''tā'' + ''asmi'' = ''bhavitāsmi'', but ''bhavi-'' + ''tā/tārāu/tāras'' = ''bhavitā/bhavitārāu/bhavitāras''. The passive forms are identical to the middle forms.
{| class="wikitable" |+ Periphrastic future |- !rowspan="2"| Person !colspan="3"| Active !colspan="3"| Middle/Passive |- ! Singular !! Dual !! Plural !! Singular !! Dual !! Plural |- ! '''1.''' | bhavitāsmi || bhavitāsvas || bhavitāsmas || bhavitāsmai || bhavitāsvahai || bhavitāsmahai |- ! '''2.''' | bhavitāsi || bhavitāsthas || bhavitāstha || bhavitāsai || bhavitāsāthai || bhavitā(sa)dhvai |- ! '''3.''' | bhavitā || bhavitārāu || bhavitāras || bhavitā || bhavitārāu || bhavitāras |}
The conditional takes secondary endings. ''{{transl|sa|-iṣya-}}'' is added to the stem, both in the active and the middle/passive. {| class="wikitable" |+ '''Conditional''' |- !rowspan="2"| Person !colspan="3"| Active !colspan="3"| Middle/Passive |- ! Singular !! Dual !! Plural !! Singular !! Dual !! Plural |- ! '''1.''' | {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyam}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyāva}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyāma}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣy(ām}})ai || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyāvahi}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyāmahi}} |- ! '''2.''' | {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyas}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyatam}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyata}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyathās}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyaithām}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyadhvam}} |- ! '''3.''' | {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyat}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyatām}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyan}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyata}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyaitām}} || {{transl|sa|ábhaviṣyanta}} |}
