The ''as'' 'to be' has the long and the short form. The long form is very rarely used. {| class="wikitable" |+ Present, Indicative |- !rowspan="3"| Person !colspan="6"| Active !!colspan="6"| Middle |- !colspan="3"| Long form !!colspan="3"| Short form !!colspan="3"| Long form !!colspan="3"| Short form |- ! Singular !! Dual !! Plural !! Singular !! Dual !! Plural !! Singular !! Dual !! Plural !! Singular !! Dual !! Plural |- ! '''1.''' | asāmi || asāvas || asāmas || asmi || svas || smas || as(ām)ai || asāvahai || asāmahai || hai || svahai || smahai |- ! '''2.''' | asasi || asathas || asatha || asi || sthas || stha || asasai || asāthai || asadhvai || sai || sāthai || dhvai |- ! '''3.''' | asati || asatas || asanti || asti || stas || santi || asatai || asātai || asantai || stai || sātai || santai |}
